Why N-grams instead of simple single word tokenization? If my goal is to identify parishes in a text, a single tokenization or 1-grams approach would fail to distinguish between St. Giles *in the Fields* and St. Giles *Without Cripplegate.* The following code block shows **an example of a tokenization process performed with [TextBlob](https://textblob.readthedocs.io/en/dev/index.html).  The `blob.noun_phrases()` method extracts nouns from a given text using the part-of-speech tagging functionality in TextBlob.  Although the method captures correctly the written abbreviation for Saint  -St- before the name of the parish -St Mary- it neither identifies the rest -at Rotherhithe- as a part of the **St. Mary Rotherhithe, nor distinguishes St. Mary Somerset from St Mary Abchurch. 

```python
blob = TextBlob(drowned_txt)
tokens = blob.noun_phrases
blob_tokens = pd.value_counts(np.array(tokens))
