I was able to capture whole parish names for most parishes by using a 6-gram vectorizer. Adjusting the `n_gram parameter` in the `CountVectorizer`  class from python’s scikit-learn library allows the extraction of sequences of words. Using a sequence of 6 words I was able to retrieve both parishes and information about the circumstances surrounding the drowning event by capturing phrases like “accidentally at st andrew in holborn” or “by oversetting of his boat at”

```python
