We can pull different combinations of 6_grams from the vectorizer and then transform them (correct spelling if necessary, eliminate unnecessary words that do not account for the parish names) to finally generate counts of the locations. In this case, I withdrew 6_grams starting with the preposition “at”, which are followed by either parish names or location names. If we remove the preposition “at” we can get all the parishes in which an drowing event took place.

